    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8293" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῥῡτήρ</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῆρος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐρύω</span>): (1)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">one who draws, drawer</span> of a bow, <i><span class="en">Od. 21.173</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            18.262</span></i>. —(2) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">guard</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 17.187</span></i> and 223.—(3) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">reins drawn tight, taut
            reins</span>, which in <i><span class="en">Il. 16.475</span></i>
          are described as having been drawn to one side and entangled by the
          fall of the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">παρήορος</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
